refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
stringeregi_replace stringpattern stringreplacement stringstring
This function is identical to ereg_replace except that this ignores case distinction when matching alphabetic characters.
&warn.deprecated.function-5-3-0.removed-6-0-0;

&reftitle.returnvalues;


 The modified string is returned. If no matches are found in 
 string, then it will be returned unchanged.

  &reftitle.examples;



    Highlight search results


<?php
$pattern = '(>[^<]*)('. quotemeta($_GET['search']) .')';
$replacement = '\\1<span class="search">\\2</span>';
$body = eregi_replace($pattern, $replacement, $body);
?>
